{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"started","call_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MbsQjaueSFWB6Quuse7tf1","tool_call":{"taskToolCall":{"args":{"description":"GEMM Compute Kernel Analysis","prompt":"You are analyzing gemm operations for a PyTorch trace on MI300X.\n\ncomparison_scope: comparative\n\n**CRITICAL - READ FIRST:**\n- Use GPU kernel time (not CPU duration) for all bottleneck analysis\n- `efficiency_percent` semantics differ by mode:\n  - **Standalone:** % of roofline. Flag > 100% as \"[ANOMALY] - verify measurement\".\n  - **Comparative:** `100 × (Trace 2 kernel time) / (Trace 1 kernel time)`.\n    - **< 100%** → Trace 1 is slower than Trace 2. **This is an optimization opportunity — flag it.**\n    - **> 100%** → Trace 2 is slower than Trace 1. **NOT an anomaly; no Trace-1 optimization needed.**\n- When citing peak performance, use bound-type-aware references: `efficiency.resolved_peak_maf` (TFLOPS) for compute-bound ops, `efficiency.resolved_peak_hbm_bw` (TB/s) for memory-bound ops\n\n**Platform Specs:**\n- Peak HBM BW: 5.3 TB/s\n- Peak references are bound-type-aware: each operation's `efficiency.resolved_peak_maf` has the precision-correct compute peak (TFLOPS); `efficiency.resolved_peak_hbm_bw` has the memory bandwidth peak (TB/s). Use the one matching `efficiency.bound_type`\n- Impact estimates assume tuning can reach 75–100% of peak performance (midpoint 87.5% used for plots)\n\n**CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS:**\n1. **Standalone:** Any efficiency > 100% → `[ANOMALY] - verify measurement`. **Comparative:** efficiency > 100% means Trace 2 is slower — NOT an anomaly; efficiency < 100% means Trace 1 is slower — flag as optimization opportunity.\n2. Status must be SUCCESS or ERROR; times in ms; efficiencies as percentages\n3. Operations with `fusion_flagged: true` in the metrics JSON are already covered by a high-confidence kernel fusion candidate — do NOT flag them as bottlenecks or write kernel_tuning recommendations. The analysis scripts already exclude them from `impact_estimates`.\n\n**Execution Context:**\n- Output directory: /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test04_gemm_mm_vs_linear/analysis_output_ref\n- Command prefix: read `/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test04_gemm_mm_vs_linear/analysis_output_ref/cache/cmd_prefix.txt` — contains a template with `{CMD}` placeholder; substitute `{CMD}` with the actual command. Since the template is just `{CMD}`, commands run directly.\n- Working directory for all commands: /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens\n\nRead and follow the FULL instructions in:\n  TraceLens/AgenticMode/Standalone/.cursor/agents/gemm-analyzer.md\n\n- Category: gemm\n- Input files: category_data/gemm_ops.csv, metadata/gemm_metadata.json, category_data/gemm_tree_data.json\n- Output file: category_findings/gemm_findings.md\n\nExecute every step in the agent file. Return \"DONE\" when complete.","subagentType":{"custom":{"name":"gemm-analyzer"}},"model":"composer-2-fast","agentId":"1ea46f13-165a-4ed1-a893-13b942c8dd34","attachments":[],"mode":"TASK_MODE_UNSPECIFIED","respondingToMessageIds":[]}}},"model_call_id":"3b861e2d-d946-44d0-b6f3-3218b841c95a-23-nmqz","session_id":"ec298410-6d6e-4ff3-a1f8-2136b81261b5","timestamp_ms":1777504727706}
