 \"**Action**\"]\n_P_ITEM_RE = re.compile(r\"^### P(\\d+):\", re.MULTILINE)\n_CANDIDATE_RE = re.compile(r\"<!-- reasoning-candidate\\s+tier=\\w+\\s+rank=(\\d+)\\s*-->\")\n_NO_ACTIONABLE_FINDINGS_MARKER = \"<!-- no-actionable-findings -->\"\n\n# Markdown table header containing an \"Args\" column. Match line that starts\n# with `|` and has `Args` as one of the column names.\n_TABLE_HEADER_RE = re.compile(r\"^\\|.*\\|\\s*Args\\s*\\|.*\\|\\s*$\", re.MULTILINE)\n\n# Level 2: cross-cutting batch checks\n_TIME_DISCREPANCY_THRESHOLD = 15  # percent\n\n# Level 3: report structure\n_REQUIRED_REPORT_HEADERS = [\n    \"Executive Summary\",\n    \"Compute Kernel Optimizations\",\n    \"Kernel Fusion Opportunities (Experimental)\",\n    \"System-Level Optimizations\",\n    \"Detailed Analysis\",\n    \"Appendix\",\n]\n_REQUIRED_METRICS_ROWS = [\n    \"Total Time\",\n    \"Compute %\",\n    \"Idle %\",\n    \"Exposed Communication %\",\n    \"Top Bottleneck Category\",\n]\n_REPORT_PLACEHOLDER_RE = re.compile(r\"<[A-Z][a-z_ ]+>\")\n_KNOWN_REPORT_PLACEHOLDERS = {\n    \"<Brief Title>\",\n    \"<Library>\",\n    \"<platform>\",\n    \"<model>\",\n    \"<architecture>\",\n    \"<scale>\",\n    \"<precision>\",\n}\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Level 1: per-file findings validation (called within each sub-agent)\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\ndef validate_findings_file(filepath, tier):","isEmpty":false,"exceededLimit":false,"totalLines":443,"fileSize":15399,"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/TraceLens/AgenticMode/Standalone/utils/validation_utils.py","readRange":{"startLine":1,"endLine":80},"relatedCursorRulePaths":[],"relatedCursorRules":[]}}}}},{"thinkingMessage":{"text":"**Generating analysis summary**\n\nI'm creating the analysis summary with no actionable findings for the kernel fusion agent template. I'm merging the title, overview, recommendations, and detailed analysis sections into a complete report format. \n\n**Reordering sections**\n\nI'm reordering the sections to match the spec, placing the Impact Summary table before Recommendations. I'm adjusting the section order to place Recommendations before Detailed Analysis as per the spec. \n\n**Analyzing findings**\n\nThe analysis shows no quantifiable savings above threshold for the candidate in `fusion_candidates.json`. ","durationMs":1871}},{"assistantMessage":{"text":"Creating `system_findings` and writing `kernel_fusion_findings.md` that merges the agent's empty-state template with required `## Recommendations` and `## Detailed Analysis` sections for validation.\n\n"}},{"toolCall":{"shellToolCall":{"args":{"command":"mkdir -p /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test04_gemm_mm_vs_linear/analysis_output_ref/system_findings","workingDirectory":"","timeout":30000,"toolCallId":"tool_b8eea507-51ad-4694-86df-5c1d4b8773f","simpleCommands":["mkdir"],"hasInputRedirect":false,"hasOutputRedirect":false,"parsingResult":{"parsingFailed":false,"executableCommands":[{"name":"mkdir","args":[{"type":"word","value":"-p"},{"type":"word","value":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test04_gemm_mm_vs_linear/analysis_output_ref/system_findings"}],"fullText":"mkdir -p /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test04_gemm_mm_vs_linear/analysis_output_ref/system_findings"}],"hasRedirects":false,"hasCommandSubstitution":false},"fileOutputThresholdBytes":"40000","isBackground":false,"skipApproval":false,"timeoutBehavior":"TIMEOUT_BEHAVIOR_BACKGROUND","hardTimeout":86400000,"description":"Ensure system_findings directory exists","closeStdin":false},"result":{"success":{"command":"mkdir -p /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test04_gemm_mm_vs_linear/analysis_output_ref/system_findings","workingDirectory":"","exitCode":0,"signal":"","stdout":"","stderr":"","executionTime":120,"interleavedOutput":"","localExecutionTimeMs":90},"isBackground":false},"description":"Ensure system_findings directory exists"}}},{"toolCall":{"globToolCall":{"args":{"targetDirectory":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals","globPattern":"**/kernel_fusion_findings.md"},"result":{"success":{"pattern":"","path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals","files":["unit_tests_comparative/test01_moe_fused_vs_unfused/analysis_output_ref/system_findings/kernel_fusion_findings.md"],"totalFiles":1,"clientTruncated":false,"ripgrepTruncated":false}}}}},{"toolCall":{"readToolCall":{"args":{"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test01_moe_fused_vs_unfused/analysis_output_ref/system_findings/kernel_fusion_findings.md"},"result":{"success":{"content":"<!--\nCopyright (c) 2024 - 2025 Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. All rights reserved.\n\nSee LICENSE for license information.\n-->\n\n# Kernel Fusion Analysis Summary (Experimental)\n\n## Overview\n\nFound 1 kernel fusion opportunity across 1 module type.\n\n> **Methodology:** Savings are measured as the total GPU time difference between trace1 and trace2, accumulated across all instances. No roofline projection is used.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### P1: 🟡 MoE fused execution path (1.16 ms, 1 instances)\n\n**Insight**: The `moe_layer` module launches four separate GPU kernels per instance on trace1 versus one fused custom GPU kernel on trace2, for one instance. The measured GPU-time gap corresponds to roughly **0.27–0.36 ms** end-to-end (**21.43–28.57%** of E2E), showing that consolidating this mixture-of-experts pipeline into fewer launches is feasible because trace2 already demonstrates a single-kernel path.\n\n**Action**: Prefer a fused mixture-of-experts implementation for this block (single launch covering routing, expert compute, and combine) where numerics and routing rules allow, mirroring the comparison trace rather than retaining the multi-kernel decomposition on trace1.\n\n**Confidence:** Medium — trace1 vs trace2 kernel counts and measured GPU-time gap are clear; kernel type metadata is coarse (`Unknown`) on this workload.\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n<!-- reasoning-candidate tier=system rank=1 -->\n\n#### MoE fused execution path (1.16 ms, 1 instances)\n\n**Identification:** Comparative fusion screening surfaced `moe_layer`: trace1 runs four distinct GPU kernels for one instance while trace2 runs one fused GPU kernel for the same module scope. (source: `fusion_candidates.json` → `module_name`, `kernel_count_trace1`, `kernel_count_trace2`, `kernels_trace1[]`, `kernels_trace2[]`)\n\n**Data:**\n\n**Trace1 kernels:**\n\n| Kernel | Type | Duration (us) |\n|--------|------|--------------|\n| moe_sorting_kernel<BF16> | Unknown | 120.0 |\n| ck_moe_stage1_kernel<BF16, 128, 128> | Unknown | 480.0 |\n| ck_moe_stage2_kernel<BF16, 128, 128> | Unknown | 480.0 |\n| moe_sum_kernel<BF16> | Unknown | 80.0 |\n\n**Trace2 kernels:**\n\n| Kernel | Type | Duration (us) |\n|--------|------|--------------|\n| triton__moe_fused_kernel_0d1d2d3d4d5d6d7d8d9d10d | Unknown | 800.0 |\n\n**Reasoning for Slowdown:** Trace1 pays for extra launches and intermediate traffic between sorting, staged expert work, and the final reduction. Trace2 completes the same logical block in one kernel, which reduces launch overhead relative to the decomposed path.\n\n**Resolution:** Fusing the mixture-of-experts stages keeps intermediate state resident across fewer synchronization points and matches the proven single-kernel structure seen on trace2 for this workload shape.\n\n**Impact estimate:**\n\n- Low end (75% gap target): 0.270 ms savings (21.43% E2E)\n- High end (100% gap target): 0.360 ms savings (28.57% E2E)\n- Fusion pattern: memory-bound, memory_bound\n- Confidence: Medium — kernel-count split and measured gap are clear; candidate typing data is coarse for some kernels\n\n## Impact Summary\n\n| Recommendation | Type | Estimated Savings (ms) | Estimated Improvement (E2E %) | Confidence |\n|----------------|------|----------------------|-------------------------------|------------|\n| MoE fused path for moe_layer | kernel_fusion | 0.27–0.36 (mid 0.315) | 21.43–28.57 | Medium |\n","isEmpty":false,"exceededLimit":false,"totalLines":66,"fileSize":3356,"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test01_moe_fused_vs_unfused/analysis_output_ref/system_findings/kernel_fusion_findings.md","readRange":{"startLine":1,"endLine":66},"relatedCursorRulePaths":[],"relatedCursorRules":[]}}}}},{"thinkingMessage":{"text":"**Reviewing test cases**\n\nI found that test01's recommendations don't include 'Impact' as a label, despite the validation requiring it for P1 issues. I'm reordering the report sections to match the spec, placing other sections before Recommendations. I'm adjusting the header order in test01 to place Impact Summary before Detailed Analysis as required by the validator. I'm correcting the test01 header order to place Detailed Analysis at the end as per the spec. ","durationMs":1694}},{"assistantMessage":{"text":"Writing the findings file: `impact_estimates` is empty — use the no-opportunities path plus spec-compliant sections.\n\n"}},{"toolCall":{"editToolCall":{"args":{"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test04_gemm_mm_vs_linear/analysis_output_ref/system_findings/kernel_fusion_findings.md","streamContent":"<!--\nCopyright (c) 2024 - 2025 Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. All rights reserved.\n\nSee LICENSE for license information.\n-->\n\n# Kernel Fusion Analysis Summary (Experimental)\n\nNo kernel fusion opportunities detected.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n<!-- no-actionable-findings -->\nNo actionable optimization opportunities identified for this category.\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n<!-- no-actionable-findings -->\nAnalysis produced no entries in `impact_estimates` after the deterministic threshold and perf-model gate. Total GPU time for the compared module matches across traces, so there is no quantifiable end-to-end savings to repo