{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"started","call_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y75PnkKE5eT7dSpgW1GUGL","tool_call":{"editToolCall":{"args":{"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test04_gemm_mm_vs_linear/analysis_output_ref/comparative_analysis.md","streamContent":"<!--\nCopyright (c) 2024 - 2025 Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. All rights reserved.\n\nSee LICENSE for license information.\n-->\n\n# Workload - Comparative Analysis: MI300X vs H100\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThis comparative analysis examines a single GEMM operation (`aten::mm`, BF16 1024×2048 × 2048×4096) executed on MI300X (Trace 1) and H100 (Trace 2). Both traces show identical kernel time (0.48 ms), indicating no performance gap between the two platforms for this workload. GPU utilization is near-optimal on both traces with negligible idle time.\n\n| Metric | Trace 1 - (MI300X) | Trace 2 - (H100) | Difference |\n|--------|----------------------------|-------------------------------|------------|\n| Total Time | 0.49 ms | 0.48 ms | -0.01 ms (-2.0%) |\n| Compute % | 97.96% | 100.00% | +2.04% |\n| Idle % | 2.04% | 0.00% | -2.04% |\n| Exposed Communication % | 0.00% | 0.00% | 0.00% |\n| Top Bottleneck Category | GEMM (97.96%) | GEMM (100.00%) | — |\n\n## Compute Kernel Optimizations\n\nFindings from per-category kernel analysis (GEMM, SDPA, elementwise, etc.).\nSummaries of recommendations from Step 7 sub-agents, focused on individual kernel efficiency.\n\n### Top Operations\n\n| Rank | Category | Trace 1 Time (ms) | Trace 2 Time (ms) | % of Compute Time | Ops | Difference (ms) | Potential improvement (time, E2E %) |\n|------|----------|-------------------|-------------------|-------------------|-----|-----------------|-------------------------------------|\n| 1 | GEMM | 0.48 | 0.48 | 100.00% | 1 | 0.00 | — |\n\n✅ No compute kernel optimization opportunities identified. All categories are within target performance bounds.\n\n---\n\n## Kernel Fusion Opportunities (Experimental)\n\n> **Note:** Kernel fusion analysis is experimental.\n\nNo kernel fusion opportunities detected.\n\n---\n\n## System-Level Optimizations\n\n> **Note:** System-level analysis is exploratory. The patterns and recommendations below are under active development and may be refined as system-level analysis matures.\n\n> **Comparative note:** System-level analysis is performed on the primary trace (Trace 1) only. Cross-trace system-level comparison is not yet supported.\n\nFindings from system-level analysis (GPU utilization, memory transfer patterns,\ncommunication/compute overlap). These affect the GPU pipeline as a whole.\n\n✅ No system-level bottlenecks detected. GPU activity breakdown shows 97.96% computation, with negligible memcpy and communication overhead.\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n### Compute Kernel Insights\n\nAnalysis completed successfully. No comparative kernel-duration gaps detected — Trace 2 kernel time equals Trace 1 for the lone GEMM operation (0.48 ms each), yielding an efficiency of 100%. No optimization opportunities to report.\n\n### Kernel Fusion Insights\n\n> **Note:** Kernel fusion analysis is experimental.\n\nNo fusion savings estimates available.\n\n### System-Level Insights\n\nNo system-level issues detected. GPU idle time is 2.04% (below the 15% threshold), with no exposed memcpy or communication overhead.\n\n---\n\n## Appendix\n\n### Model Architecture\n- **Model**: Cannot be inferred from trace\n- **Architecture**: Cannot be inferred from trace\n- **Scale**: Cannot be inferred from trace\n- **Precision**: BF16\n\n### Hardware Reference\n- **Platform**: MI300X\n- **Peak HBM BW**: 5.3 TB/s\n- **Peak MAF (BF16)**: 708 TFLOPS\n- **Peak MAF (FP8)**: 1273 TFLOPS\n"}}},"model_call_id":"3b861e2d-d946-44d0-b6f3-3218b841c95a-71-mdbh","session_id":"ec298410-6d6e-4ff3-a1f8-2136b81261b5","timestamp_ms":1777504859220}
