-level analysis is exploratory. The patterns and recommendations below are under active development and may be refined as system-level analysis matures.\n+\n+> **Comparative note:** System-level analysis is performed on the primary trace (Trace 1) only. Cross-trace system-level comparison is not yet supported.\n+\n+Findings from system-level analysis (GPU utilization, memory transfer patterns,\n+communication/compute overlap). These affect the GPU pipeline as a whole.\n+\n+✅ No system-level bottlenecks detected. GPU activity breakdown shows 97.96% computation, with negligible memcpy and communication overhead.\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Detailed Analysis\n+\n+### Compute Kernel Insights\n+\n+Analysis completed successfully. No comparative kernel-duration gaps detected — Trace 2 kernel time equals Trace 1 for the lone GEMM operation (0.48 ms each), yielding an efficiency of 100%. No optimization opportunities to report.\n+\n+### Kernel Fusion Insights\n+\n+> **Note:** Kernel fusion analysis is experimental.\n+\n+No fusion savings estimates available.\n+\n+### System-Level Insights\n+\n+No system-level issues detected. GPU idle time is 2.04% (below the 15% threshold), with no exposed memcpy or communication overhead.\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Appendix\n+\n+### Model Architecture\n+- **Model**: Cannot be inferred from trace\n+- **Architecture**: Cannot be inferred from trace\n+- **Scale**: Cannot be inferred from trace\n+- **Precision**: BF16\n+\n+### Hardware Reference\n+- **Platform**: MI300X\n+- **Peak HBM BW**: 5.3 TB/s\n+- **Peak MAF (BF16)**: 708 TFLOPS\n+- **Peak MAF (FP8)**: 1273 TFLOPS","afterFullFileContent":"<!--\nCopyright (c) 2024 - 2025 Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. All rights reserved.\n\nSee LICENSE for license information.\n-->\n\n# Workload - Comparative Analysis: MI300X vs H100\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThis comparative analysis examines a single GEMM operation (`aten::mm`, BF16 1024×2048 × 2048×4096) executed on MI300X (Trace 1) and H100 (Trace 2). Both traces show id